    • Field Detail

      • generalInventory

        public static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,Animal> generalInventory
        A data container that stores all the general inventory data for all animals in the shelter. The supervisors input the data to the program and the program then takes that data, saves it in the form of an object, and stores it. The shelter supervisors can then search for animals by case number. When the program is closed, the inventory is purged.

      • getDogBreeds

        public static java.lang.String[] getDogBreeds()
                                       throws java.io.IOException
        Retrieves the list of dog breeds from the file DOGBREEDS.CSV and lists them in a string array that contains each breed's unique integer identifier and name. Data for breeds is stored in this format: numerical identifier,name,weight,hair color,hair length. This file can be edited. Reads the file by generating a string array for every line in the file, then making a list of these string arrays. Then creates a new string array the same size as the list of string arrays containing a string in the format "numerical identifier-name"
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • writeToCSV

        public static void writeToCSV(java.util.List<java.lang.String[]> dataset,
              java.lang.String filepath)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        Takes a list of string array objects and writes it to a CSV file using the OpenCSV library. Data is written as string arrays where each element in the array is separated by a comma. This method replaces every entry previously in the file.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if bad things happen during the writing or the initialization of the writer.

      • populateInventoryHashMaps

        public static void populateInventoryHashMaps()
                                      throws java.io.IOException
        Upon initialization of the application, this method goes through the CSV files that contain the inventory information for the animals in the shelter, extracts them as objects, and places them in the inventory hashmaps. These animals can then be searched later through the hashmap. It does this by writing the CSV file GENERAL_INVENTORY.csv to a list, then going through each entry to determine the type. From there, it searches the specific inventory CSV files for the matching data. When the data is found, it then parses the arrays into animal objects and inserts them into the hashmap.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if bad things happen during the extraction process.

      • mapDataToCSV

        public static void mapDataToCSV()
                         throws java.io.IOException
        Updates the CSV files using the data from the Hashmaps. This method replaces every entry previously in the CSV files with the updated entries.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if bad things happen during the writing or with the initialization of the writer.
